      <section id="wellness" class="section-card">
        <h2>Wellness and Support Programs</h2>
        <p>These programs offer support for physical health, emotional well-being, disease management, counseling, surgery and cancer care navigation, and employee discounts.</p>
        <div class="bullet-grid">
          <div class="bullet-item">Sharecare wellness program</div>
          <div class="bullet-item">RealAge Test and wellness incentives for eligible members</div>
          <div class="bullet-item">Emotional Wellbeing Solutions (EWS) through Optum</div>
          <div class="bullet-item">Carrum Health Centers of Excellence</div>
          <div class="bullet-item">Employee Discount Program</div>
          <div class="bullet-item">Working for a Healthier Tennessee (State employees only)</div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="enrollment" class="section-card featured">
        <div class="section-intro-tag">Start here</div>
        <h2>Enrolling in Coverage</h2>
        <p>As a new employee, you have 30 days from your hire date to elect benefits. Day 1 counts toward the 30-day deadline.</p>
        <p>Your agency benefits coordinator will tell you how to enroll, usually through Employee Self-Service (ESS) or, if allowed by your agency, by paper form.</p>
        <p>If you enroll dependents, you must provide dependent verification documents during enrollment.</p>
        <div class="timeline" aria-label="Enrollment timeline infographic">
          <div class="timeline-step" data-step="1">
            <h3>Review your options</h3>
            <p>Compare medical, dental, vision and any other benefits available to you.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-step" data-step="2">
            <h3>Choose who to cover</h3>
            <p>Select your coverage level and decide whether you are enrolling dependents.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-step" data-step="3">
            <h3>Gather documents</h3>
            <p>Collect any required dependent verification before you start enrollment.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-step" data-step="4">
            <h3>Enroll within 30 days</h3>
            <p>Submit your elections on time through ESS or your agency’s approved process.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bullet-grid">
          <div class="bullet-item">Spouse: marriage certificate, plus an additional document if married more than 12 months</div>
          <div class="bullet-item">Dependent children: birth certificates</div>
          <div class="bullet-item">Stepchildren: marriage verification and birth certificate or legal relationship document</div>
        </div>
        <div class="note"><strong>Important:</strong> A full list of acceptable documents is available on the Partners for Health website.</div>
        <div class="resource-grid" aria-label="Helpful resources">
          <div class="resource-card">
            <h3>Benefit comparison chart</h3>
            <p>Use this resource to compare plan costs, deductibles, copays and out-of-pocket limits before you enroll.</p>
            <a class="resource-link" href="#cost-terms">View comparison details</a>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-card">
            <h3>Carrier and network choices</h3>
            <p>Review the BCBS and Cigna network options and check provider participation before making a selection.</p>
            <a class="resource-link" href="#carriers-networks">Review networks</a>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-card">
            <h3>Dependent verification checklist</h3>
            <p>Make sure you have the right documents ready if you plan to enroll a spouse, child or stepchild.</p>
            <a class="resource-link" href="#enrollment">See document list</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
